<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What are the most popular plastic surgery procedures in 2026?</h3>
<p>The most popular procedures in 2026 include non-surgical treatments like fillers and Botox, gynecomastia surgery for men, body contouring procedures, facial rejuvenation surgeries, and hair transplantation. Non-surgical options continue to grow in demand due to their minimal downtime and natural results.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Are non-surgical procedures as effective as surgery?</h3>
<p>Non-surgical procedures can produce excellent results for mild to moderate concerns. However, for significant skin laxity, excess fat, or structural changes, surgical procedures often provide more dramatic and long-lasting outcomes. A consultation with Dr. Manoj K Johar can help determine which approach is best suited to your specific needs.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is plastic surgery safe for men?</h3>
<p>Yes, plastic surgery is equally safe for men when performed by a qualified, board-certified surgeon. Men may have different anatomical considerations, and experienced surgeons adjust their techniques accordingly. Dr. Johar has extensive experience treating male patients and achieving natural, masculine results.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long do non-surgical results typically last?</h3>
<p>The longevity of non-surgical results varies by treatment. Botox typically lasts 3 to 6 months, dermal fillers may last 6 to 18 months depending on the product, and laser treatments may require maintenance sessions every 6 to 12 months. Your surgeon can provide specific guidance based on the treatments recommended for you.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What is regenerative medicine in plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Regenerative medicine involves using biological therapies like stem cells, platelet-rich plasma (PRP), and growth factors to enhance healing and rejuvenate tissues. These treatments can complement surgical and non-surgical procedures, improving results and reducing recovery time.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I combine multiple procedures in one surgery?</h3>
<p>Yes, combination procedures are increasingly popular and can be performed safely when planned appropriately. Combining procedures reduces overall recovery time and can be more cost-effective. Dr. Manoj K Johar will evaluate your health and goals to determine if a combined approach is safe and beneficial for you.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do I choose the right procedure for my goals?</h3>
<p>The best way to determine the right procedure is through a comprehensive consultation with a qualified plastic surgeon. During this consultation, your surgeon will assess your anatomy, discuss your goals, and recommend treatments that align with your expectations. Schedule a consultation by calling +91 85277 78462.</p>
</div>
</div>

